'''Sarutahiko-no-Oh-Kami''' is a [[kami]], a deity of the [[Japan|Japanese]] religion of [[Shinto]].

Sarutahiko is a powerful guradian kami whom is enshrined in the name of Tsubaki Jinja and the Tsubaki Grand Shrine of America. he is the leader of earthy kami and guarding of the floating bridge of heaven. He appears in the Kojiki (recored of ancient matters) number of times along with his wife Ame-No-Uzume. sarutahiko is depicted as a towering man with a large beard, jeweled spear, and distinctive nose. Sarutahiko is also a figur of strength and willpower. This is depicted in a section of Kojiki that describes the Grandson of the Sun Goddess, Amaterasu who is ready to take control of the world. He refuses to leave earth untill his soon-to-be wife, Ame-No-Uzume comes provocitively to convincehim to change his mind. Today, most american shintoists are devout followers in the teachings of Sarutahiko for many are associated with the Tsubaki Grand Shrine of America.

