'''Sarutahiko-no-Oh-Kami''' (サルタヒコ), is a [[kami]], a deity of the [[Japan|Japanese]] religion of [[Shinto]].

Sarutahiko is a powerful guardian kami who is enshrined at Tsubaki Jinja in Mie Prefecture and at Sarutahiko Jinja in Ise.  In the Kojiki, he is the leader of the earthly kami who greets Ninigi, the grandson of Amaterasu, the Sun Goddess, when he descends from Takamagahara.  He is depicted as a towering man with a large beard, jewelled spear, and distinctive nose.  At first he is unwilling to yield his realm until persuaded by Ame-No-Uzume, the deity of dance, whom he afterwards married.  The kami is seen as a symbol of strength and guidance, which is why he is the patron of martial arts such as aikido.  

