{{Short description|Diety in Shinto; leader of the earthly kami}} {{For|the asteroid|10768 Sarutahiko}} {{Shinto}} '''Sarutahiko Ōkami''' (猿田毘古大神, 猿田彦大神), is the leader of the earthly [[kami]], deity of the [[ethnic religion|Japanese religion]] of [[Shinto]]. [[Norito]] also mentions him with the title ''Daimyōjin'' (大明神 great bright god, or greatly virtuous god) instead of Ōkami (大神 great god). Sarutahiko Ōkami was the head of the [[kunitsukami]].<ref>{{Cite book|last=Picken|first=Stuart D. B.|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=xlG3F6gSm9UC&newbks=0&printsec=frontcover&pg=PA76&dq=Sarutahiko+earth+kami&hl=en|title=Historical Dictionary of Shinto|date=2010-12-28|publisher=Scarecrow Press|isbn=978-0-8108-7372-8|pages=76|language=en}}</ref>
